==History== The Twenty Melbourne Painters Society (TMPS) was established in 1918.<ref name="ArtAlmanac">{{cite web|title=Twenty Melbourne Painters Society Inc: The 95th Annual Exhibition|url=http://www.art-almanac.com.au/twenty-melbourne-painters-society-inc-the-95th-annual-exhibition/|website=Art Almanac|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref> The group was a break-away group from the [[Victorian Artists Society]], leaving to follow [[Australian Tonalism|Australian Tonalist]] [[Max Meldrum]].<ref name="History">{{cite web|title=History|url=http://twentymelbournepainterssociety.com.au/home/history/|website=Twenty Melbourne Painters Society Inc|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>
In 1919, within the first year of formation, the Twenty Melbourne Painters held their first exhibition.<ref name="JennyPihan">{{cite web|title=Tradition of Excellence that Began with Artistic Rebellion.|url=http://www.jennypihanfineart.com.au/content.asp?p=artists%7CTWENTY%20MELBOURNE%20PAINTERS%20SOCIETY%20INC.|website=Jenny Pihan Fine Art|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>
The group is limited to 20 members<ref name="weekendnotes">{{cite web|title=98th Twenty Melbourne Painters Society's Annual Exhibition|url=https://www.weekendnotes.com/twenty-melbourne-painters-societys-annual-exhibition/|website=weekend notes|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref> and is by invitation.<ref name="JennyPihan"/>
The Twenty Melbourne Painters has held an annual exhibition since 1919.<ref name="tmps">{{cite web|title=the Twenty Melbourne Painters Society|url=http://twentymelbournepainterssociety.com.au/|website=Twenty Melbourne Painters Society Inc|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>
