{{Infobox NRHP | name = Z.C.B.J. Opera House | nrhp_type = | image = ZCBJ Opera House from W.JPG | caption = | location= 4th Avenue and Main St., [[Verdigre, Nebraska]] | coordinates = {{coord|42|35|48.4|N|98|2|0|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Nebraska#USA | built = 1900 | architecture = [[Baroque architecture]] | added = May 16, 1988 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 88000946<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalregisterofhistoricplaces.com/NE/Knox/state.html |title=Z.C.B.J. Opera House |publisher=[[National Register of Historic Places]] |accessdate=2011-08-29}}</ref> }} The '''Z.C.B.J. Opera House''' is a building in [[Verdigre, Nebraska]], United States, that was built in 1903. It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1988. It serves as a meeting hall for the [[Czech American|Czech community]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nebraskahistory.org/histpres/nebraska/knox/KX14-001-ZCBJOperaHouse.pdf |title=National Register of Historic Places Registration Form |publisher=[[United States Department of the Interior]] |accessdate=2011-08-29}}</ref>
